‘Rest’ means any
uninterrupted period during which the driver may freely dispose of his
time;

‘Reduced daily
rest period’ means any period of rest of at least 9 hours but
less than 11 hours;

‘Weekly driving
time’ means the total accumulated driving time during a
week;

Vehicles used for the carriage of passengers on
regular services where the route covered by the service in question
does not exceed 50 kilometres;

Vehicles
used in emergencies or rescue operations, including the non-commercial
transport of humanitarian aid;

Vehicles undergoing road tests for technical
development, repair or maintenance purposes, and new or rebuilt
vehicles which have not yet been put into service;

Vehicles with a maximum permissible mass not
exceeding 7.5 tonnes used for non-commercial carriage of
goods;

Daily
and weekly driving periods, interruptions and daily and weekly rest
periods;

Weekly
rest periods and driving periods between these rest
periods;

Compensation
for weekly rest periods reduced in accordance with article 8, paragraph
6;

in the event of a change of vehicle during
a working day (reading on the vehicle to which he was assigned and reading
on the vehicle to which he is assigned);

The
record sheets for the current week and those used by the driver in the
previous 15 calendar days;

Any manual record and printout made during the
current week and the previous 15 calendar days, as required under this
Agreement;

The periods
referred to in article 12, paragraph 3, second indent, points(b), (c)
and (d);

„Rust”:
een ononderbroken tijdvak gedurende hetwelk de bestuurder vrijelijk
over zijn tijd kan beschikken;

„Verkorte dagelijkse rusttijd”: een
rustperiode van ten minste 9 uren, doch minder dan 11
uren;

„Normale wekelijkse
rusttijd”: een rustperiode van ten minste 45
uren;

“Wekelijkse
rijtijd”: de totale gedurende een week opgetelde
rijtijd;

voertuigen bestemd voor het vervoer van personen
